        <updateDate>2021-05-20T12:26:47Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Businesses Preparing for a Better Tomorrow Act</b></p> <p>This bill allows employers a payroll tax credit in each calendar quarter of 50% of the their qualified workplace training expenses paid or incurred after March 12, 2020, and before January 1, 2021. The bill defines <i>qualified workplace training expenses</i> as employer expenses for education and training for the health and safety of employees in the workplace with respect to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019), and the prevention of the spread of COVID-19 in the workplace. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
